         <div type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <p>Здесь лежит Трофим.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Here lies Trophimos.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary" xml:lang="ru">
            <p> Надпись найдена недалеко от <ref type="inscription">V 290</ref><!--byz279--> и <ref type="inscription">V 302</ref><!--byz296--> и близка, 
               как сообщает Шкорпил, им по шрифту. Камень был приобретен для Мелек-Чесменского музея.</p>
                <p> 1–3. Относительно формулы см. <ref type="introduction">IV.3.F.d</ref>.  </p>
            <p>4–5. Имя Трофим было распространено не только на христианском Боспоре 
               (ср. <ref type="inscription">V 285</ref><!--byz273-->, <ref type="inscription">V 289</ref><!--byz277-->, 
               <ref type="inscription">V 301</ref><!--byz295-->, 
               <ref type="inscription">V 331</ref><!--byz310-->), где прежде не 
               было известно, но и в Херсоне (ср. комм. к <ref type="inscription">V 49</ref><!--byz049-->).</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
            <p>The inscription was found not far from <ref type="inscription">V 290</ref><!--byz279--> and <ref type="inscription">V 302</ref><!--byz296-->
               and resembled them in script, according to Shkorpil. The monument was acquired for Melek-Chesmen Tumulus Museum.</p>
            <p>   </p>
            <p> 1–3. On the formula, see Introduction <ref type="introduction">IV.3.F.d</ref>.  </p>
            <p>4–5. The name Trophimos is widely attested not only in Christian Bosporus (<ref type="inscription">V 285</ref><!--byz273-->, 
               <ref type="inscription">V 289</ref><!--byz277-->, <ref type="inscription">V 301</ref><!--byz295-->, <ref type="inscription">V 331</ref><!--byz310-->), 
               where it had not been known before, but also in Cherson (cf. commentary to  <ref type="inscription">V 49</ref><!--byz049-->).</p>
         </div>
